			<td>206</td><td>Aqua</td><td>Aqua (formerly EOS PM-1)</td><td>NASA, JAXA, INPE</td><td>Operational (extended)</td><td>04 May 2002</td><td>Sep 2026</td><td>6-year nominal mission life, currently in extended operations. Atmospheric dynamics / water and energy cycles, cloud formation, precipitation and radiative properties, air / sea fluxes of energy and moisture, sea ice extent and heat exchange with the atmosphere. The HSB instrument failed on the 5th of February 2003.</td><td>AIRS, AMSR-E, AMSU-A, CERES, HSB, MODIS</td><td>347, 664, 1555, 397, 442, 395</td><td>Sun-synchronous</td><td>705 km</td><td>98.8 mins</td><td>98.2 deg</td><td>16</td><td>13:50</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Ascending</td><td>https://eospso.nasa.gov/missions/aqua</td><td>https://search.earthdata.nasa.gov/search?q=AQUA&amp;ok=AQUA</td>
