			<td>207</td><td>Aura</td><td>Aura (formerly EOS Chemistry)</td><td>NASA, NSO, FMI, NIVR, UKSA</td><td>Operational (extended)</td><td>15 Jul 2004</td><td>Sep 2025</td><td>6-year nominal mission life, currently in extended operations. Measurements of aerosol and cloud properties for climate predictions, using a 3-channel lidar and passive instruments in formation with CloudSat for coincident observations of radiative fluxes and atmospheric state.</td><td>HiRDLS, MLS (EOS-Aura), OMI, TES</td><td>351, 126, 630, 349</td><td>Sun-synchronous</td><td>705 km</td><td>98.8 mins</td><td>98.2 deg</td><td>16</td><td>13:46</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Ascending</td><td>http://aura.gsfc.nasa.gov/</td><td>https://search.earthdata.nasa.gov/search?q=AURA</td>
