			<td>836</td><td>FLEX</td><td>FLuorescence EXplorer</td><td>ESA</td><td>Approved</td><td>Apr 2027</td><td>Dec 2030</td><td>FLEX will provide global maps of vegetation fluorescence that can reflect photosynthetic activity and plant health and stress. This is not only important for a better understanding of actual photosynthetic efficiency, the status of vegetation health and plant performance and of the global carbon cycle, but also for agricultural management and food security.</td><td>FLORIS</td><td>1778</td><td>Sun-synchronous</td><td>814 km</td><td>101 mins</td><td>98.64 deg</td><td>27</td><td>10:00</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>Ascending</td><td>https://earth.esa.int/eogateway/missions/flex</td><td>&nbsp;</td>
