			<td>1459</td><td>Geo-S2</td><td>Geostationary Extended Observations Sounder 2</td><td>NOAA</td><td>Approved</td><td>Nov 2040</td><td>Dec 2055</td><td>GeoXO will supply vital information to address major environmental challenges of the future in support of U.S. weather, ocean, and climate operations. The GeoXO mission will continue and expand observations provided by the GOES-R Series as NOAA&#39;s next generation of geostationary satellites.</td><td>ACX, GXS</td><td>2048, 2049</td><td>Geostationary</td><td>36000 km</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>&nbsp;</td><td>N/A</td><td>https://www.nesdis.noaa.gov/next-generation-satellites/geostationary-extended-observations-geoxo</td><td>&nbsp;</td>
